dict.string: Deposits any drawing that is taking place onto the drawing page.
For whatever mode the nozzle is in, subtracts values or elements from the result.
For whatever mode the nozzle is in, adds values or elements to the result.
Turns the shading shapes mode on and off.
Pushes the palette's settings to the selected object(s).
Pulls the selected object settings to the palette.
Makes the current representation mode a stroke.
Makes the current representation mode a solid fill.
Makes the current representation mode a solid fill and stroked.
Makes the current representation mode the custom setting.
When this mode is toggled on, drawn strokes will have their line processed with perlin noise.
Changes the brush tip to an ellipse. Produces brush stroke shapes (i.e. closed bezier paths).
Changes the brush tip to a rectangle. Produces brush stroke shapes (i.e. closed bezier paths).
Changes the brush tip to be uniform. Produces brush stroke shapes (i.e. closed bezier paths).
Changes the brush tip to be a bezier path. Produces bezier paths (not shapes, like the other brush tips).
Changes the brush tip to be a bezier path, makes it stroke only, and makes it 1pt.
Draws a rounded corner by depositing two B-Spline points
Cycles through the three rounded corner options: arc, b-spline, and bevel.
Moves the current live point to the stroke's first point, making a closed shape.
Deposits three B-Spline points to make a hard corner.
Deposits three B-Spline points to make a hard corner, then bows the following line.
Deposits three B-Spline points to make a hard corner, then bows the following line.
During live drawing, erases the last point deposited. This allows for correcting real-time mistakes.
Dabs one brush tip onto the drawing.
Cancels whatever live activity is taking place.
Cancels whatever live activity is taking place.
Shows and hides the cropping frame that is used for export and printing.
Adjusts the nearest corner of the export frame.
Adjusts the center point of the export frame.
Deposits three B-Spline points to make a round corner, then bows the following line.
Exports the export frame immediately to disk.
Exports the selected objects immediately to disk.
Exports the canvas immediately to disk.
If drawing: stamps the current line segment. If selected objects: stamps the objects. If perspective mode is on: stamps vanishing points guidelines.
Draws an ellipse based on two axes, by default. Configurable under "Shape Keys" in the Drawing Settings Panel.
Draws a rectangle from two lines of the perimeter, by default. Configurable under "Shape Keys" in the Drawing Settings Panel.
All subpaths are separated into different objects and then made the selection.
Draws a shape inside four points of a quadrilateral. Configurable under "Shape Keys" in the Drawing Settings Panel.
Takes the selected paths and joins them in the order they were selected.
Activates the list of sections for the Drawing Settings Panel.
Draws arcs like a drafting compass.
Places the selected objects into a group. To ungroup, press Control + Shift + G.
Any grouped objects in the selection will be ungrouped.

Makes an arc from deposited points. If starting a stroke, this key is pressed three times at different points. If a point has been deposited, press this key two times (in two separate point locations).
Deposits three B-Spline points to make a round corner, then bows the following line.
Deposits lines leading to the vanishing point.
Turn on and off the vanishing point lines snapping. Active only when perspective mode is on.
Turn on and off the vanishing point lines, including horizon line.
Removes all lines leading to the vanishing point that were deposited by the user.
Show and hide keyboard panel that sits inside the document window.
Show and hide the paint mode tray that sits inside the document window.
Show and hide the layers panel.
Connects the current live point to the stroke's first point, making a closed shape.
When there is a selection of objects, this repositions the purple anchor point where the cursor is located. The selection anchor point is used as the reference for rotation and scaling operations.
Begins or ends selecting objects with the selection rectangle.
The permanent anchor point is saved inside the document and it is used by the Replication Mode. Go to "Anchor Points" section for options. It is green in color.
If there is a selection with only one object, that object can use its own anchor point instead of the regular anchor every time it is selected. It is red in color.
Turns replication mode on and off. Replication mode is configured in the Drawing Settings panel.
Replicate the selected objects according to the settings in the Replication Mode box.
Moves the Azimuth clockwise by 5 degrees.
Moves the Azimuth clockwise by 15 degrees.
Moves the Azimuth clockwise by 15 degrees.
Moves the Azimuth clockwise by 45 degrees
Increases the Azimuth by its step amount.
Increases the Azimuth by its step amount.
Moves the azimuth clockwise by 45 degrees
Decreases the current stroke scale by a step amount.
Decreases the current stroke scale by a smaller step amount.
Decreases the current stroke scale by a larger step amount.
Decreases the current stroke scale by a step amount.
Decreases the current stroke scale by a larger step amount.
Decreases the current stroke scale by a smaller step amount.
Decrements the stroke width, either the selected objects or settings.
Decrements the stroke width, either the selected objects or settings.
Increments the stroke width, either the selected objects or settings.
Increments the stroke width, either the selected objects or settings.
Select objects. Equivalent to pressing the mouse button plus shift.
Begin or end carting. Carting locks selected objects to the location of the cursor until the spacebar is pressed again.
Delete all strokes on the current layer.
Turns snapping of angles on lines on and off.
Turns snapping of grid points on and off.
Steps the current layer toward the base layer.
Moves the selected objects to the front.
Moves the selected objects to the back.
Increase hue for basic hues in palette keys.
Decrease brightness for basic hues in palette keys.
Decrease saturation for basic hues in palette keys.
Increase saturation for basic hues in palette keys.
Layer Step Away From Base Layer
Steps the current layer away from the base layer.
Increases the width of the brush tip.
Increases the height of the brush tip.
Sets the brush angle at 90 degrees.
Decreases the height of the brush tip.
Decreases the width of the brush tip.
Sets the brush angle at 0 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 0 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 180 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 180 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 270 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 45 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 135 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 225 degrees.
Sets the brush angle at 315 degrees.
Shows and hides the grid (as configured in the Settings panel).
Turns snapping of line lengths to a fixed increment.
Turns snapping of the current mouse point to existing points on the drawing layer.
Turns snapping of the current mouse point to existing stroke paths on the drawing layer.
Turns snapping of the current mouse point to alignment points and segments.
Loads the currently selected object(s) into the loaded object slot.
All selected shapes that overlap will be joined together. If there are no selected shapes, this changes the live combinatorics mode to union.
Change the live combinatorics mode to union.
Change the live combinatorics mode to subtraction.
Change the live combinatorics mode to intersection.

One selected object is subtracted from all other selected objects. The object that was selected last is the negative object. If there are no selected shapes, this changes the live combinatorics mode to subtraction.
The intersection of all selected shapes will be produced. If there are no selected shapes, this changes the live combinatorics mode to intersection.
